        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-05T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-05T07:00:00-05:00" n="549"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1590: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-05T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 5, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 5—10:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>423. A communiqué has just been issued giving the text of the following telegram
                    from Suvich to the Secretary General dated October 5.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“I have the honor to inform you that the reports from Ethiopian sources
                        concerning bombardments by Italian aircraft of inhabited areas causing
                        victims among the civil population and of a Red Cross hospital at Adowa are
                        devoid of all foundation. All that happened was that a few Italian airplanes
                        on a reconnaissance flight having encountered heavy fire from anti-aircraft
                        batteries and rifles dropped a few bombs on parties of soldiers. It should
                        also be pointed out that there is no Red Cross hospital or ambulance at
                        Adowa. There was one Italian ambulance which discontinued its work on the
                        departure of our Consul,”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
